    "abstractNote": "The tombstone of the Christian bishop Mar Solomon is an important witness to communities of the Church of the East and Manichaeans in fourteenth-century China. The epitaph consists of a bilingual inscription in Chinese and Syro-Turkic. Three major points will be discussed\u2014the identification of Mar Solomon as administrator of both communities; the use of the term \u201cManzi\u201d to designate Mar Solomon\u2019s geographical area of influence; and the significance of the style and languages of the epitaph.",
